// Regression floor: implicit memberwise construction (bug #38) must reject a
// call that supplies MORE positional arguments than the class has assignable
// data fields. Before the fix, the surplus args were silently dropped at
// runtime and the value diverged across engines (IR zero-inited an int to "0";
// the tree-walker / LLVM / emit-C++ left an empty object stringifying to "").
// A primitive has zero data fields, so ANY argument is too many.
void run() {
    console.writeln(int(3.9).toString());   // int has 0 data fields, 1 arg
}
run();
